Concise rules for using the Vibecamp design system. Use MUST/SHOULD/NEVER to guide decisions.

## Components

- Component selection
  - MUST: Prefer components from [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/) over custom implementations
  - NEVER: Create custom implementations when design system components exist
  - MUST: Use design system components instead of creating custom implementations

## Colors & Tokens

- Semantic color tokens
  - MUST: Use semantic color tokens instead of hardcoded colors
  - MUST: Use tokens like `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, and `bg-muted`
  - NEVER: Use hardcoded color values (hex, rgb, hsl) directly in components
  - MUST: Reference CSS variables defined in [globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)

## Component Variants

- Variant usage
  - MUST: Use the built-in variant system for consistent styling
  - MUST: Use component variants like `default`, `outline`, `destructive`, `ghost` for buttons
  - MUST: Use `secondary` variant for badges when appropriate
  - SHOULD: Apply hover effects with `hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow` for cards

## Utilities

- Class management
  - MUST: Use the `cn()` utility from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) for conditional classes
  - MUST: Import `cn` from `@/lib/utils` for proper class merging
  - NEVER: Use manual class concatenation (template literals or string concatenation)
  - MUST: Use `cn()` for combining conditional and static classes

